palities of the Philippines|Municipalities]]''': [[Albuera, Leyte|Albuera]], [[Bato, Leyte|Bato]], [[Baybay, Leyte|Baybay]], [[Hilongos, Leyte|Hilongos]], [[Hindang, Leyte|Hindang]], [[Inopacan, Leyte|Inopacan]], [[Matalom, Leyte|Matalom]], [[Ormoc City|Ormoc]] <small>(became city 1947)</small>, [[Kananga, Leyte|Kananga]] <small>(established 1950)</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:40%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"40%\"| Period\n! Representative<ref name=roster/>\n|-\n| <small>[[9th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1931&ndash;1934\n| Pacifico Yba\u00f1ez\n|-\n| <small>[[10th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1934&ndash;1935\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Dominador M. Tan\n|-\n| <small>[[1st National Assembly of the Philippines|1st National Assembly]]</small><br />1935&ndash;1938\n|-\n| <small>[[2nd National Assembly of the Philippines|2nd National Assembly]]</small><br />1938&ndash;1941\n|-\n| <small>[[1st Congress of the Commonwealth of the Philippines|1st Commonwealth Congress]]</small><br />1945\n|-\n| <small>[[1st Congress of the Philippines|1st Congress]]</small><br />1946&ndash;1949\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Domingo Veloso\n|-\n| <small>[[2nd Congress of the Philippines|2nd Congress]]</small><br />1949&ndash;1953\n|-\n| <small>[[3rd Congress of the Philippines|3rd Congress]]</small><br />1953&ndash;1957\n|-\n| <small>[[4th Congress of the Philippines|4th Congress]]</small><br />1957&ndash;1961\n| Alberto Aguja\n|}\n\n=== 1961\u20131972 ===\n*'''[[Municipalities of the Philippines|Municipalities]]''': [[Alangalang, Leyte|Alangalang]], [[Barugo, Leyte|Barugo]], [[Burauen, Leyte|Burauen]], [[Capoocan, Leyte|Capoocan]], [[Carigara, Leyte|Carigara]], [[Dagami, Leyte|Dagami]], [[Jaro, Leyte|Jaro]], [[Julita, Leyte|Julita]], [[La Paz, Leyte|La Paz]], [[Pastrana, Leyte|Pastrana]], [[Tabontabon, Leyte|Tabontabon]], [[Tunga, Leyte|Tunga]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:40%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"40%\"| Period\n! Representative<ref name=roster/>\n|-\n| <small>[[5th Congress of the Philippines|5th Congress]]</small><br />1961&ndash;1965\n| Primo \"Olong\" Avestruz Villasin\n|-\n| <small>[[6th Congress of the Philippines|6th Congress]]</small><br />1965&ndash;1969\n| Salud Vivero Parre\u00f1o{{efn|group=1e|Died on December 27, 1969, three days before end of term.}}\n|-\n|<small>[[7th Congress of the Philippines|7th Congress]]</small><br />1969&ndash;1972\n| ''vacant''{{efn|group=1e|Salud Vivero Parre\u00f1o was re-elected in the [[1969 Philippine House of Representatives elections|1969 elections]] for a second term, but died before the opening of the 7th Congress. No special election was held to fill the seat vacancy.<ref name=\"roster\"/>}}\n|}\n'''Notes'''\n{{notelist|group=1e}}\n\n== 3rd District ==\n<!-- This section is linked from [[1st National Assembly of the Philippines]] -->\n*'''[[Municipalities of the Philippines|Municipalities]]''': [[Calubian, Leyte|Calubian]], [[Leyte, Leyte|Leyte]], [[San Isidro, Leyte|San Isidro]], [[Tabango, Leyte|Tabango]], [[Villaba, Leyte|Villaba]]\n*'''Population (2015)''': 179,594\n[[Image:Ph fil congress leyte 3d.png|right|200px|thumb|Map of the current 3rd District of Leyte]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:40%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"40%\"| Period\n! Representative<ref name=roster/>\n|-\n| <small>[[10th Congress of the Philippines|10th Congress]]</small><br />1995&ndash;1998\n| Alberto S. Veloso\n|-\n| <small>[[11th Congress of the Philippines|11th Congress]]</small><br />1998&ndash;2001\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Eduardo K. Veloso\n|-\n| <small>[[12th Congress of the Philippines|12th Congress]]</small><br />2001&ndash;2004\n|-\n| <small>[[13th Congress of the Philippines|13th Congress]]</small><br />2004&ndash;2007\n|-\n| <small>[[14th Congress of the Philippines|14th Congress]]</small><br />2007&ndash;2010\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Andres D. Salvacion, Jr.\n|-\n| <small>[[15th Congress of the Philippines|15th Congress]]</small><br />2010&ndash;2013\n|-\n| <smal