5\" />}}\n|-\n| <small>[[13th Congress of the Philippines|13th Congress]]</small><br />2004&ndash;2007\n|-\n| <small>[[14th Congress of the Philippines|14th Congress]]</small><br />2007&ndash;2010\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<small>[[15th Congress of the Philippines|15th Congress]]</small><br />2010&ndash;2013\n| [[Lucy Torres|Lucy Marie T. Gomez]]{{efn|group=1a|Disqualified by the [[Supreme Court of the Philippines|Supreme Court]] on March 19, 2013 for being ineligible to run for office as substitute of [[Richard Gomez]].<ref name=\"roster\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lawphil.net/judjuris/juri2013/mar2013/gr_202202_2013.html |title=G.R. No. 202202 - SILVERIO R. TAGOLINO, Petitioner, vs. HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES ELECTORAL TRIBUNAL AND LUCY MARIE TORRES-GOMEZ, Respondents. |date=19 March 2013 |accessdate=4 August 2019 |author=Supreme Court of the Philippines}}</ref> Seat remained vacant until the end of 15th Congress.}}\n|-\n| ''vacant''\n|-\n| <small>[[16th Congress of the Philippines|16th Congress]]</small><br />2013&ndash;2016\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Lucy Torres|Lucy Marie T. Gomez]]\n|-\n| <small>[[17th Congress of the Philippines|17th Congress]]</small><br />2016&ndash;2019\n|-\n| <small>[[18th Congress of the Philippines|18th Congress]]</small><br />2019&ndash;2022\n|}\n'''Notes'''\n{{notelist|group=1a}}\n\n=== 1907\u20131931 ===\n*'''[[Municipalities of the Philippines|Municipalities]]''': [[Alangalang, Leyte|Alangalang]], [[Babatngon, Leyte|Babatngon]], [[Dulag, Leyte|Dulag]], [[Palo, Leyte|Palo]], [[Tacloban]], [[Tanauan, Leyte|Tanauan]], [[Tolosa, Leyte|Tolosa]], [[San Miguel, Leyte|San Miguel]] <small>(re-established 1909)</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:40%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"40%\"| Period\n! Representative<ref name=roster/>\n|-\n| <small>[[1st Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1907&ndash;1909\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Jaime C. De Veyra]]\n|-\n| <small>[[2nd Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1909&ndash;1912\n|-\n| <small>[[3rd Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1912&ndash;1916\n| Francisco D. Enage\n|-\n| <small>[[4th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1916&ndash;1919\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Ruperto Kapunan\n|-\n| <small>[[5th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1919&ndash;1922\n|-\n| <small>[[6th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1922&ndash;1925\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Filomeno Montejo\n|-\n| <small>[[7th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1925&ndash;1928\n|-\n| <small>[[8th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1928&ndash;1931\n| Cirilo Bayaya\n|}\n\n=== 1931\u20131961 ===\n*'''[[Municipalities of the Philippines|Municipalities]]''': [[Abuyog, Leyte|Abuyog]], [[Babatngon, Leyte|Babatngon]], [[Dulag, Leyte|Dulag]], [[Palo, Leyte|Palo]], [[San Miguel, Leyte|San Miguel]], [[Tacloban]] <small>(became city 1954)</small>, [[Tanauan, Leyte|Tanauan]], [[Tolosa, Leyte|Tolosa]], [[Santa Fe, Leyte|Santa Fe]] <small>(established 1949)</small>, [[MacArthur, Leyte|MacArthur]] <small>(established 1954)</small>, [[Mayorga, Leyte|Mayorga]] <small>(established 1955)</small>, [[Mahaplag, Leyte|Mahaplag]] <small>(established 1957)</small>, [[Javier, Leyte|Bugho]] <small>(established 1961)</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:40%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"40%\"| Period\n! Representative<ref name=roster/>\n|-\n| <small>[[9th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1931&ndash;1934\n| Cirilo Bayaya\n|-\n| <small>[[10th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1934&ndash;1935\n| Fortunato M. Sevilla\n|-\n| <small>[[1st National Assembly of the Philippines|1st National Assembly]]</small><br />1935&ndash;1938\n| Francisco D. Enage\n|-\n| <small>[[2nd National Assembly of the Philippines|2nd National Assembly]]</small><br />1938&ndash;1941\n| Norberto Romualdez\n|-\n| <small>[[1st Congress of the Commonwealth of the Philippines|1st Commonwealth Congress]]</small><br />1945\n| Filomeno Montejo\n|-\n| <small>[[1st Congress of the Philippines|1st Congress]]</small><br />1946&ndash;1949\n| Juan R.