]], [[Caibiran, Biliran|Caibiran]], [[Kawayan, Biliran|Kawayan (Almeria)]], [[Leyte, Leyte|Leyte]], [[Merida, Leyte|Merida]], [[Naval, Biliran|Naval]], [[Ormoc City|Ormoc]], [[Palompon, Leyte|Palompon]], [[San Isidro, Leyte|San Isidro]], [[Biliran, Biliran|Biliran]] <small>(re-established 1909)</small>, [[Villaba, Leyte|Villaba]] <small>(re-established 1909)</small>, [[Maripipi, Biliran|Maripipi]] <small>(re-established 1914)</small>, [[Albuera, Leyte|Albuera]] <small>(re-established 1917)</small>, [[Calubian, Leyte|Calubian]] <small>(re-established 1919)</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:40%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"40%\"| Period\n! Representative\n|-\n| <small>[[1st Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1907&ndash;1909\n| Quiremon Alkuino\n|-\n| <small>[[2nd Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1909&ndash;1912\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Estanislao Granados\n|-\n| <small>[[3rd Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1912&ndash;1916\n|-\n| <small>[[4th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1916&ndash;1919\n| Manuel Veloso\n|-\n| <small>[[5th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1919&ndash;1922\n| Francisco D. Enage\n|-\n| <small>[[6th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1922&ndash;1925\n| Carlos S. Tan\n|-\n| <small>[[7th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1925&ndash;1928\n| Juan Veloso\n|-\n| <small>[[8th Philippine Legislature]]</small><br />1928&ndash;1931\n| Bernardo Torres\n|}\n\n=== 1931\u20131961 ===\n*'''[[Municipalities of the Philippines|Municipalities]]''': [[Biliran, Biliran|Biliran]], [[Caibiran, Biliran|Caibiran]], [[Calubian, Leyte|Calubian]], [[Kawayan, Biliran|Kawayan]], [[Leyte, Leyte|Leyte]], [[Maripipi, Biliran|Maripipi]], [[Merida, Leyte|Merida]], [[Naval, Biliran|Naval]], [[Palompon, Leyte|Palompon]], [[San Isidro, Leyte|San Isidro]], [[Villaba, Leyte|Villaba]], [[Isabel, Leyte|Isabel]] <small>(re-established 1947)</small>, [[Almeria, Biliran|Almeria]] <small>(re-established 1948)</small>, [[Cabucgayan, Biliran|Cabucgayan]] 